          <table width="950" border="0" cellspacing="10" cellpadding="0">
            <tr>
              <td align="left" valign="top"><h1>How to Obtain  Your Benefit Reimbursement 
                </h1>
                <ul type="disc">
                  <li>Call us to initiate a claim. </li>
                  <li>Then call the certified tire       store of your choice. Take your vehicle to your pre-selected certified tire       store.</li>
                  <li>Once you have selected a tire       store, you must have the service technician contact our department to       finalize your claim. </li>
                  <li>Once approved you will receive       an authorization number.</li>
                  <li>Obtain an itemized receipt for       the service performed. Please write the authorization number and       membership number on the original paid receipt (not a photocopy) and send       it within 60 days* to: </li>
                </ul>
                <p>N2Plus Roadside Care<br>
                  Attn: Claims  Department <br>
                  1009 N Palm Canyon <br>
                  Palm    Springs,   CA 92262</p>
                <h2>PLEASE NOTE:</h2>
                <ul type="disc">
                  <li>YOU       MUST RECEIVE PRIOR AUTHORIZATION FROM THE CLAIMS CENTER       BEFORE ANY ROADSIDE SERVICE, REPAIRS OR REPLACEMENT HAS BEGUN. REIMBURSEMENTS       WILL BE ISSUED 4-6 WEEKS FROM THE DATE WE RECEIVE ALL DOCUMENTS REQUIRED</li>
                </ul>
                <h2>EXCLUSIONS:</h2>
                <ul type="disc">
                  <li>Tire failure outside the United States and Canada.</li>
                  <li>Tire damage resulting from       vehicle collision, vandalism, dry rot, acts of God, fire or flood.</li>
                  <li>Tire manufacturer defects,       theft, recapped tires, racing tires, snow tires, tires with less than       three/thirty seconds (3/32) of an inch of thread depth.</li>
                  <li>Normal wear or tire issues due       to maintenance such as alignment or balancing, abnormal wear caused by       misalignment or suspension problems are not covered.</li>
                  <li>Driving vehicles other than       off-road motorcycles /ATV&rsquo;s on unpaved roads are excluded.</li>
                  <li>Vehicles used commercially are       excluded.</li>
                  <li>Tires needing to be replaced       and/or repaired due to Curb/SIDEWALL damage are not covered.</li>
                  <li>Expenses for ancillary services       like mounting, balancing, and valve stems are not covered.</li>
                  <li>Claims postmarked more than 60       days after the service date will not be honored. No time limit for Utah and Wisconsin       residents.</li>
                </ul></td>
              </tr>
          </table>
